description:
&lt;p&gt;Community CAMHS North serves the Newark and Sherwood and Bassetlaw Nottinghamshire areas. Clinical bases include the 65 Northgate in Newark and Langold near Worksop.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community CAMHS Service supports Children, Young People and their families/carers with their emotional and mental health needs on a continuum of mild to severe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be involved in the development of the new CAMHS service following the publication of Future In Mind.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Community CAMHS CBT Therapist will work as a member of the North Community CAMHS Team and contribute to the multidisciplinary team. There is currently a 1 WTE post fixed term within the team. The post holder will be responsible for an agreed caseload and will contribute to all aspects of team functioning as required. Both individual work, group facilitation and supervision of trainees and junior staff members will be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work with a variety of agencies including adult service providers to ensure a quality service is provided. You must be a Registered Nurse, Dip SW or equivalent social work qualification (CSS, CQSW, degree in social work), Allied Health Professional registered with the HCPC and accredited by a HCPC recognised body e.g. UKCP/BACP.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full UK driving licence and vehicle for business use is required for this post; however reasonable adjustments will be made for disabled individuals in line with the Equality Act 2010.&lt;/p&gt;
